Step 1: Determine Total Liabilities and Total Owner's Equity at the end of the reporting period.
• Total Liabilities: From the balance sheet, the Total Current Liabilities is 7,605,149.91. (There are no additional non-current liabilities provided, so we use this figure.)
• Total Owner's Equity: The End_amount is 16,112,375.10.

Step 2: Calculate the Debt to Equity Ratio.
Debt to Equity Ratio = Total Liabilities / Total Owner's Equity
= 7,605,149.91 / 16,112,375.10

Step 3: Perform the division.
7,605,149.91 ÷ 16,112,375.10 ≈ 0.47

Thus, the Debt to Equity Ratio as of the end of the reporting period is approximately 0.47.
